===Etymology===
Since 16th century; from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|epilepsie|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|la}} {{term|epilepsia|epilēpsia|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|ἐπιληψία|tr=epilēpsia|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}}, from {{term|ἐπιλαμβάνω||I seize|tr=epilambanō|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}}, from {{term|ἐπί||upon|tr=epi|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}} + {{term|λαμβάνω||I take|tr=lambanō|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈɛpɪlɛpsi/}}, {{X-SAMPA|/"EpIlEpsi/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|epilepsies}}

# {{pathology}} A medical [[condition]] in which the sufferer experiences [[seizure]]s (or [[convulsion]]s) and [[blackout]]s.

